# Document Docker Labs 5.1 and 5.2 in devops-field-guide

## What was completed

Document two completed Docker labs from the IITC DevOps course.

### Lab 5.1: Custom NGINX Image with Custom Config
Topic: Dockerfile, custom Nginx configuration, custom HTML, port mapping, troubleshooting

What was completed:
- Created a custom Docker image based on nginx:1.27.0
- Fixed an incorrect Dockerfile that originally did not copy nginx.conf or index.html into the image
- Used a custom nginx.conf that listens on port 8080
- Copied nginx.conf into /etc/nginx/nginx.conf
- Copied index.html into /usr/share/nginx/html/index.html
- Built image custom-nginx:3.0
- Ran container my-nginx-v2 with port mapping 8080:8080
- Verified with curl http://localhost:8080
- Final response:
  <h1>LAB 5.1 - Custom NGINX</h1>
  <p>Port 8080</p>

Key troubleshooting:
- Empty reply from server happened because the Dockerfile did not copy nginx.conf and index.html into the image
- Dockerfile build output only showed:
  FROM nginx:1.27.0
  RUN apt-get update && apt-get install -y nano
- After adding COPY instructions, the lab worked
- Important distinction:
  - Full nginx.conf with events and http blocks belongs in /etc/nginx/nginx.conf
  - conf.d/default.conf should usually contain only server blocks

Final Dockerfile for Lab 5.1:
FROM nginx:1.27.0
RUN apt-get update && apt-get install -y nano
COPY nginx.conf /etc/nginx/nginx.conf
COPY index.html /usr/share/nginx/html/index.html
EXPOSE 8080

Commands used:
- docker build -t custom-nginx:3.0 .
- docker rm -f my-nginx-v2
- docker run -d -p 8080:8080 --name my-nginx-v2 custom-nginx:3.0
- curl http://localhost:8080
- docker logs my-nginx-v2
- docker ps

