### Lab 5.2: Copying a Custom index.html into a Docker Image
Topic: Dockerfile COPY, default Nginx document root, image rebuilds, Docker cache, Linux ownership, chown

What was completed:
- Created a clean lab directory:
  E:\Genspark\DevOps-Materials\Docker\lab5.2-copy-index
- Created a local index.html:
  <h1>LAB 5.2 - Custom index.html</h1>
  <p>Copied into nginx image</p>
- Built an initial image without COPY:
  lab52-nginx:1.0
- Ran a container on port 80:
  lab52-nginx-before
- Verified default Nginx page with curl http://localhost
- Added COPY instruction to Dockerfile:
  COPY index.html /usr/share/nginx/html/index.html
- Rebuilt image with the same tag:
  lab52-nginx:1.0
- Ran container:
  lab52-nginx-after
- Verified custom HTML with:
  curl -i http://localhost
- Checked file ownership inside the container using:
  MSYS_NO_PATHCONV=1 docker exec lab52-nginx-after ls -l /usr/share/nginx/html/index.html
- Saw initial ownership:
  root root
- Added permission fix:
  RUN chown nginx:nginx /usr/share/nginx/html/index.html
- Rebuilt image again
- Ran final container:
  lab52-nginx-final
- Verified final result:
  HTTP/1.1 200 OK
  <h1>LAB 5.2 - Custom index.html</h1>
  <p>Copied into nginx image</p>
- Verified final ownership:
  -rwxr-xr-x 1 nginx nginx 68 ... /usr/share/nginx/html/index.html

Final Dockerfile for Lab 5.2:
FROM nginx:1.27.0
RUN apt-get update && apt-get install -y nano
COPY index.html /usr/share/nginx/html/index.html
RUN chown nginx:nginx /usr/share/nginx/html/index.html

Commands used:
- docker build -t lab52-nginx:1.0 .
- docker rm -f lab52-nginx-before 2>/dev/null || true
- docker run -d -p 80:80 --name lab52-nginx-before lab52-nginx:1.0
- curl http://localhost
- docker stop lab52-nginx-before
- docker rm lab52-nginx-before
- docker images | grep -E 'lab52-nginx|<none>'
- docker run -d -p 80:80 --name lab52-nginx-after lab52-nginx:1.0
- curl -i http://localhost
- MSYS_NO_PATHCONV=1 docker exec lab52-nginx-after ls -l /usr/share/nginx/html/index.html
- docker stop lab52-nginx-after
- docker rm lab52-nginx-after
- docker run -d -p 80:80 --name lab52-nginx-final lab52-nginx:1.0
- MSYS_NO_PATHCONV=1 docker exec lab52-nginx-final ls -l /usr/share/nginx/html/index.html
- docker ps

Important Git Bash note:
- Git Bash on Windows may rewrite Linux container paths like /usr/share/nginx/html/index.html into Windows paths such as C:/Program Files/Git/usr/share/nginx/html/index.html
- Fix:
  MSYS_NO_PATHCONV=1 docker exec ...

Important learning notes:
- docker exec runs commands inside the container, but Docker CLI commands like docker stop must be run from the host, not from inside the container
- Docker Hub tokens are unrelated to local docker build, docker run, docker exec, or localhost curl testing
- 403 Forbidden may happen when Nginx cannot read the copied file because of ownership or permissions
- In this run there was no 403 because the file was still readable, but ownership was fixed anyway according to the lab requirement
- Nginx master process often runs as root, while worker processes usually run as nginx
- COPY adds files into the image during build
- RUN chown changes ownership inside the image during build
- Docker cache behavior observed:
  - FROM was cached
  - RUN apt-get install nano was cached
  - COPY was cached when index.html did not change
  - RUN chown was rebuilt after being added

